{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016mHF9pv2fTAdQ9gMWdTnW5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze each behavior for the spreadsheet formula engine and determine the minimum test level needed.\n\n1. **SUM(A1:A10) evaluates correctly**\n   - This is about evaluating a range formula. It's pure algorithmic logic — parsing the range, summing values.\n   - MOCK-MISS: Single function evaluation, no module boundary crossing needed\n   - REAL-INFRA: No OS/network/subprocess needed\n   - LLM-DEP: No AI/ML\n   - MULTI-STEP: No\n   - Minimum: Unit — this is purely algorithmic, can test with in-memory cells\n\n\n2. **Cascaded formula resolution (=B1+1 where B1=A1*2)**\n   - This involves multiple cells interacting through dependency resolution, which crosses module boundaries between the formula parser and cell reference resolver. It's integration-level because the failure mode only appears when cells hand off data to each other, even though everything stays in-process within the engine.\n   - Actually, if the whole formula engine is a single unit, I could test cascading formulas with just one object, making this unit-level. The real question is whether I can catch the failure with a minimal test of the engine itself.\n   - I'll go with Unit — I can write a test that creates cells and verifies cascading resolution works correctly within the formula engine object.\n\n3. **Circular dependency detection**\n   - This is graph traversal logic for detecting cycles in the dependency graph — pure algorithm work.\n   - Minimum: Unit\n\n4. **VLOOKUP exact match and error when not found**\n   - This is straightforward function implementation testing.\n   - Minimum: Unit\n\n5. **IF with nested conditions**\n   - Pure expression evaluation logic.\n   - Minimum: Unit\n\n6. **CONCATENATE with empty cell handling**\n   - The specific behavior here is skipping empty cells instead of inserting blanks, which is a pure function concern.\n   - Minimum: Unit\n\n7. **Cross-sheet reference resolution**\n   - This requires multiple sheet objects working together with the formula resolver, so the failure only surfaces when sheets hand off data to each other.\n   - Minimum: Integration\n\n8. **Recalculation in topological order when a**\n   - The dependency graph, change propagation, and formula evaluator all need to coordinate to ensure cells recalculate in the right order.\n   - Minimum: Integration\n\n9. **Undo operation restores formula text and computed dependent values**\n   - The undo/redo system, formula engine, and dependency graph need to work together to restore both the original formula and all downstream values.\n   - Minimum: Integration\n\n10. **Save/load workbook produces identical values**\n    - This involves actual file I/O with a custom binary format, though it could be tested with in-memory byte buffers instead of hitting the real filesystem.\n    - Minimum: Integration or System — the core failure mode is about serialization correctness and floating-point precision, which would surface with a temp file or BytesIO just as well as real disk I/O.\n\nNow let me step back and reconsider the earlier ones... -memory cells\n2. Cascaded formula resolution — Integration: needs formula evaluator + cell reference resolver to interact\n3. Circular dependency — Unit: pure graph algorithm\n4. VLOOKUP — Unit: pure function logic\n5. IF nested — Unit: pure expression evaluation\n6. CONCATENATE — Unit: pure function logic\n7. Cross-sheet reference — Integration: needs sheet manager + formula resolver\n8. Topological recalculation — Integration: needs dependency graph + change propagation + evaluator\n9. Undo/redo — Integration: needs undo stack + formula engine + dependency graph\n10. Save/load — Integration: serialization/deserialization with file I/O (could use tempfile)\n\nFor save/load, BytesIO would catch the same bugs as real filesystem reads for deterministic serialization, so I'll classify it as Integration. On cascaded formulas, the formula engine as a single module could handle cascaded evaluation, but since the reference resolver needs to work with the evaluator, that's module interaction. For SUM(A1:A10), the formula engine needs to parse the range, look up values, and sum them — if it's a single module, that's Unit, but if parsing and lookup are separate modules, it's Integration. I'll keep most as Unit since they're algorithmic functions within the formula engine, with Integration reserved for cross-module dependencies like cross-sheet references and cascading recalculation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9771,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9771},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c23cf374-d253-4fb9-ad4c-77b627a99216","uuid":"7025ceb9-12c8-4615-b213-e2dd76d2e064"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016mHF9pv2fTAdQ9gMWdTnW5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HkEK3D1ZuYGtZqCxBEgCid","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"=SUM(A1:A10) evaluates to the correct sum of cells A1 through A10","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: This tests a single formula evaluation path — range parsing, cell value lookup, and arithmetic — all within the formula engine object. The failure mode is algorithmic (wrong sum, wrong range parsing), not a module-boundary handoff. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network needed. LLM-DEP: None. MULTI-STEP: No. A unit test can construct an in-memory cell grid, assign values to A1:A10, and assert the evaluated result. REJECTION-GATE: Integration would require a separate module boundary to be crossed — but the behavior is about the formula evaluator's internal logic, not a handoff between distinct subsystems.","test_description":"Construct an in-memory cell grid with numeric values in A1:A10, set a formula cell to =SUM(A1:A10), invoke evaluate(), and assert the result equals the expected sum. Also test edge cases: all zeros, single cell, mixed positive/negative.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A formula referencing another formula cell (=B1+1 where B1=A1*2) produces the correct cascaded result","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure here only surfaces when the formula parser, cell reference resolver, and evaluator cooperate — specifically when the evaluator must recursively resolve an intermediate formula cell before completing its own computation. This is a module-boundary handoff (reference resolver hands formula cells back to the evaluator). A unit test of any single module in isolation cannot reproduce this. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) No OS/network. (b) No AI/ML. (c) No multi-agent. Stays at Integration.","test_description":"Wire together the formula parser, cell graph, and evaluator. Create cells: A1=5, B1==A1*2, C1==B1+1. Call evaluate on C1 and assert it returns 11. Vary A1 and verify C1 updates correctly through the chain.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Circular dependency (A1 refs B1, B1 refs A1) is detected and returns a circular reference error instead of looping","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Cycle detection is a graph algorithm applied to the dependency graph — a single, self-contained data structure. The failure mode (infinite loop or stack overflow) appears within the cycle-detection logic itself, not at a boundary between distinct modules. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. REJECTION-GATE: Integration would require this to fail only when two modules hand off state — but the cycle detector operates on the dependency graph as a unit.","test_description":"Construct a dependency graph with A1 depending on B1 and B1 depending on A1. Invoke the cycle detection or evaluation entry point and assert the result is a CircularReferenceError (or equivalent), not a hang or exception. Test a 3-node cycle as well.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.78,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"VLOOKUP exact match returns correct value; returns error when key is not found","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: VLOOKUP is a built-in function whose logic — scan a table range for a matching key, return the Nth column — is self-contained within the function implementation. Both the match path and the not-found path are algorithmic branches inside one function. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. REJECTION-GATE: No distinct module boundary is crossed; the lookup table is an in-memory cell range passed to the function.","test_description":"Build an in-memory lookup table (e.g., a 4x2 cell range with keys and values). Call VLOOKUP with a key that exists and assert the correct column value is returned. Call VLOOKUP with a missing key and assert the expected error (#N/A or equivalent) is returned. Test boundary: key at first and last row.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"IF correctly handles nested conditions (=IF(A1>10, IF(A1>20, 'high', 'medium'), 'low'))","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Nested IF evaluation is pure expression tree traversal within the formula evaluator — the failure mode (wrong branch taken, wrong result) is algorithmic, not a module-boundary issue. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. REJECTION-GATE: No distinct module boundary is crossed; the entire IF tree is evaluated by the expression evaluator alone.","test_description":"Set A1 to each of three representative values (e.g., 5, 15, 25) and evaluate =IF(A1>10, IF(A1>20, 'high', 'medium'), 'low'). Assert the results are 'low', 'medium', and 'high' respectively. Also test boundary values (10, 20) for edge-case branch selection.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"CONCATENATE joins cell values with correct separator and skips empty cells rather than inserting blank strings","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The behavior describes two specific algorithmic rules inside the CONCATENATE function: separator insertion and empty-cell filtering. Both are implementable and testable as internal function logic. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. REJECTION-GATE: No module boundary is required; the function takes a list of resolved cell values and applies string operations.","test_description":"Call CONCATENATE with a mix of non-empty and empty cell values. Assert that (a) non-empty values are joined with the correct separator, and (b) empty cells produce no blank entry in the output (the separator does not appear for them). Test all-empty case, single-value case, and adjacently empty cells.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"A cross-sheet reference (=Sheet2!A1+1) resolves correctly when the referenced sheet exists","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure mode only surfaces at the boundary between the formula evaluator and the workbook/sheet manager: the evaluator must request a cell from a *different sheet object*, which requires the sheet registry to locate Sheet2 and return its cell. A unit test of the evaluator alone with a stubbed sheet lookup would not reveal bugs in the actual sheet dispatch path. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) No OS. (b) No AI. (c) No multi-agent. Stays at Integration.","test_description":"Create a workbook with two in-memory sheets. Set Sheet2!A1 = 10. On Sheet1, evaluate =Sheet2!A1+1 and assert the result is 11. Also test that referencing a non-existent sheet returns the appropriate #REF! error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"When a referenced cell's value changes, all dependent formulas recalculate in correct topological order","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure — wrong order of recalculation, stale intermediate values — only emerges when the dependency tracker, topological sorter, and formula evaluator cooperate on a live cell change event. No single module in isolation can exhibit this bug; it requires the change-notification path to wire through all three subsystems. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) No OS. (b) No AI. (c) No multi-agent. Stays at Integration.","test_description":"Build a dependency chain: A1 (value), B1==A1*2, C1==B1+3. Change A1 and trigger recalculation. Assert B1 and C1 are updated in dependency order and hold correct values. Add a diamond dependency (D1==A1+B1) to verify the topological sort handles a shared ancestor correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"Undo after editing a formula restores both the formula text and all previously computed dependent values","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure requires the undo stack, formula evaluator, and dependency recalculation subsystem to interact: after undo the engine must restore the formula text *and* re-evaluate all downstream cells to their prior results. A bug in any one of these modules' interaction (e.g., undo restores formula text but triggers a stale recalculation) only appears when all three are wired together. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) No OS. (b) No AI. (c) No multi-agent. Stays at Integration.","test_description":"Set A1=5, B1==A1*2 (evaluates to 10). Edit B1's formula to ==A1+100 (evaluates to 105). Call undo(). Assert B1's formula text is restored to ==A1*2 and its computed value is 10. Verify a dependent of B1 (e.g., C1==B1+1) also returns to its prior value of 11.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.87,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Saving and loading a workbook produces identical cell values and formulas with no data loss or floating-point precision change","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure (data loss, precision change) is in the serialization/deserialization pipeline — multiple modules (serializer, binary formatter, deserializer, cell reconstruction) must cooperate. REAL-INFRA: The core precision and data-loss bugs are in the binary encoding logic, not in OS-level file behavior; a tempfile or BytesIO write/read cycle reproduces the exact failure mode without real filesystem I/O. An in-process round-trip test using BytesIO or a tempfile is sufficient. REJECTION-GATE for System: the behavior's failure mode is not about OS buffering, permissions, or real file handle lifecycle — it is about the correctness of the binary format. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) Tempfile suffices — no real OS behavior needed. (b) No AI. (c) No multi-agent. Stays at Integration.","test_description":"Build a workbook with cells containing integer values, floating-point values (with many decimal places), formula strings, and empty cells. Serialize to a BytesIO buffer (or tempfile). Deserialize a new workbook from that buffer. Assert each cell's formula text and computed value are bit-for-bit identical to the originals. Include a cell with a value like 1/3 to verify floating-point precision is preserved.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9771,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9771},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c23cf374-d253-4fb9-ad4c-77b627a99216","uuid":"7aef7632-7021-446f-a8c2-9a171ee2e196"}
